description: string
This field specifies the full name of the protein recommended by UniProt consortium
This field provides an abbreviation of the full name or an acronym of the protein recommended by UniProt consortium
Synonym of the recommended name [full name] of protein in UniProt consortium
Synonym of the recommended name [short name] of protein in UniProt consortium.
This field indicates the name(s) of the gene that code for the protein sequence in UniProt consortium.
constraints: Four distinct tokens exist: 'Name'; 'Synonyms'; 'Ordered locus names' and 'ORF names'.

description: A unique identifier assigned to a isoform chosen to be the canonical sequence in UniProt consortium
constraints: The identifier is composed of primary accession number which consists of 6-10 alphanumeric charaters; followed by a dash and a number

description: The sequence of the protein in the FASTA format
A unique identifier assigned to a keyword in UniProt consortium
The unique identifier assigned to a transcript in ENSEMBL database
The unique identifier assigned to a protein in ENSEMBL database
A unique identifier assigned to protein in RCSB PDB database.
constraints: The alphanumeric identifier starts with a digit

description: Resolution of structures that were determined by X-ray crystallography or electron microscopy.
This field provides the structure determination method of the protein from RCSB PDB database
General description of the function(s) of a protein from UniProt consortium
This field describes the status[Reviewed] of the UniProtKB accession
constraints: The boolean value will be Yes-Reviewed

description: This field describes the status[Unreviewed] of the UniProtKB accession
constraints: The boolean value will be No-Unreviewed

description: This field indicates the identifier of a specific organism in NCBI taxonomic database
constraints: Unique identifier assigned to species name

description: Name of the Keyword in UniProt consortium
Mass of the protein in daltons from UniProt consortium
This field indicates the chain(s) of the determined structure from RCSB PDB database
This field indicates corresponding range of the determined structure from RCSB PDB database
This field indicates the entry name of the sequence.
The field provides information if a given UniProtKB accession is canonical or not. Yes- Canonical; No- Not Canonical
This field identifies the UniProtKB accession as reviewed or unreviewed. Yes-Reviewed No-Unreviewed.
This field provides cross reference identifiers from UniProt consortium. Where x denotes the cross reference database. Eg: PDB; RefSeq; HGNC; Pfam etc

This field provides cross reference label[name] associated with the cross reference identifiers from UniProt consortium. Where X denotes the cross reference database. Eg: REACTOME; InterPro; PROSITE etc.
This field provides gene symbol from HGNC database.
Name of the saccharide from Uniprot consortium.
Name of the amino acid.
This field provides information about the type of glycosylation associated with the site on the canonical protein sequence.
This field provides information about the site of glycosylation found in canonical protein sequence from UniProt consortium.
